<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2883] Bug in AntBuilder - DemuxOutputStream should be used</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2883</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a problem in AntBuilder - output from some tasks is not redirected to Ant, but is stilll printed out to STDERR.&lt;br/&gt;
Thus it is impossible to use Ant logging subsystem to redirect output to log file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For instance, javac warnings are printed directly to console (actually, to STDERR).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ant itself uses DemuxOutputStream for STDOUT and STDERR redirection.&lt;br/&gt;
AntBuilder uses DemuxInputStream for input handling, but it does not redirect output streams.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
